whether they were white.

00:42:38.910 --> 00:42:41.910
However you define -
however they defined white,

00:42:41.910 --> 00:42:43.410
but in the nineteenth century, no.

00:42:43.410 --> 00:42:47.620
And in every census form
they're always white,

00:42:47.620 --> 00:42:49.420
always considered to be white.

00:42:49.420 --> 00:42:53.980
So there was no problem and really
it's kind of astonishing to me.

00:42:53.980 --> 00:42:59.880
They had really good friends
in Tennessee called the McTeers

00:42:59.880 --> 00:43:03.140
and there was once a critical
article written about one

00:43:03.140 --> 00:43:06.870
of their performances and Mr.
McTeer wrote an angry letter

00:43:06.870 --> 00:43:09.380
to the newspaper defending them

00:43:09.380 --> 00:43:12.790
and saying not only was
the performance authentic,

00:43:12.790 --> 00:43:15.920
but the family was a fantastic
family and that people should get

00:43:15.920 --> 00:43:17.950
to know them because
they were wonderful.

00:43:17.950 --> 00:43:21.060
So they were really, to me,

00:43:21.060 --> 00:43:25.550
amazingly quickly accepted
in Tennessee.

